      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MOONLIGHT MILLER (2) pinged the lids from out wide but run ended and faded out of it late when 5th at Sandown in Grade 4/5 company. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Can make amends. KEEN ON KEV (1) was an impressive winner last time in quickest of the meeting when scoring by 2.5 lengths (27.29) at Horsham. Capable of going close again. ASTON YAMATO (8) broke well and quickly mustered speed to win over the 425m at Bendigo two runs back then settled forward again when finishing second at Bendigo last start. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from five starts. Expected to be in the finish again. OVER ACHIEVER (6) has strong claims after a top-three finish in good time last time out.",
